   =20
      Font detectives
   =20
 =20

Craig Wright is a guy who says he is=C2=A0Satoshi Nakamoto, the pseudonymou=
s=C2=A0inventor of Bitcoin, and who is involved in litigation with the Cryp=
to Open Patent Alliance, which says he isn=E2=80=99t.  Here is a post from =
the Bitcoin Legal Defense Fund claiming that several of the documents =E2=
=80=9Con which [Wright] primarily relies in support of his claim to be Sato=
shi=E2=80=9D might be forgeries. The alleged evidence includes =E2=80=9Cmet=
adata showing the documents that Dr. Wright claims were written in 2008 wer=
e edited with software (Grammarly, MathType, OpenOffice.org, Code2Flow) and=
 fonts (Calibri Light and Nirmala UI) that didn=E2=80=99t yet exist,=E2=80=
=9D as well as =E2=80=9Cmetadata showing that Satoshi Nakamoto=E2=80=99s na=
me had been replaced with Wright=E2=80=99s name on the Bitcoin White Paper,=
 by editing it around 2019 using Adobe software.=E2=80=9D
I have to say that it would be useful if someone could invent a method of s=
toring electronic information in a permanent, immutable, provably incorrupt=
ible way! Of course that wouldn=E2=80=99t be very helpful here, though, unl=
ess the person had invented it in 2008.=C2=A0

