<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am probably=C2=A0<em>the=C2=A0</em>person in=
 the world who was most susceptible to Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s =E2=80=
=9Cactually it=E2=80=99s complicated=E2=80=9D defense of the collapse of hi=
s crypto exchange, FTX Trading:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I love for things to be complicated!<=
/li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I have, if I do say so myself, a p=
retty robust sense of humor about fraud, particularly crypto fraud.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I have met Bankman-Fried and liked him, a=
nd actually <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/332741=
79.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItM=
DYtMDEvY3J5cHRvLWNsZWFyaW5nLWFuZC1jcmVkaXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RV=
RkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTA=
2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb5e7ef7b" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">  found his arguments</a> about real-time automated futures margining com=
pelling.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I have written a lot abou=
t things =E2=80=94=C2=A0the breakdown in the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMzAvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1=
uaWNrZWwtbWFya2V0LWFsbW9zdC1icm9rZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG=
1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDYmdXRtX=
2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7b2e6d53" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  nic=
kel market</a>=C2=A0last year, the collapse of <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0d=
XAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1=
dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN=
0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb4dd220c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Silicon Valley Bank</a=
>=C2=A0earlier this year =E2=80=94=C2=A0that have approximately the same=C2=
=A0shape as the collapse of FTX, but=C2=A0<em>without=C2=A0</em>any fraud.<=
/li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So when SBF <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9v=
cGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDIvc2JmLXMtZGVmZW5zZS13aWxsLWJlLXRvdWdoP2N=
tcGlkPUJCRDExMDYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZX=
dzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB424af5d5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">  was like</a> =E2=80=9Csee, I was running=
 a leveraged financial institution that took customer deposits for margin t=
rades and leveraged futures bets; I was doing what I thought was reasonable=
 risk management, but then a once-in-a-lifetime storm crashed the crypto ma=
rkets and a run on the bank evaporated my customers=E2=80=99 money,=E2=80=
=9D I was pretty much the ideal audience for that pitch.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still there were two huge problems with that p=
itch. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259=
412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTItMTM=
vaG93LXRvLWRvLWZyYXVkLWF0LWEtZnV0dXJlcy1leGNoYW5nZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA2MjNfTU=
9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVyb=
T0yMzExMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4cc5872=
b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  One is</a> that it was not, on its own terms,=C2=A0true. You=
 could imagine a world in which Bankman-Fried was right, one where FTX=E2=
=80=99s=C2=A0terms of service made it clear that he was allowed to reinvest=
 customer money, where FTX=E2=80=99s good-faith risk management was overwhe=
lmed by a market crash. It=E2=80=99s just that in the actual world none of =
that was true. The terms of service did not say that,=C2=A0Bankman-Fried wa=
s taking insane risks with customer money and lying about it constantly, an=
d FTX=E2=80=99s apparently pretty good risk management engine was just=C2=
=A0<em>turned off=C2=A0</em>when it came to Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s own tra=
ding firm, Alameda Research, which took and lost all that customer money. A=
lso FTX=E2=80=99s insurance fund that was meant to protect customer deposit=
s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDkvb3p=
lbXBpYy1pcy1iYWQtZm9yLWJ1c2luZXNzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDYyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV=
9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEwNiZ1dG1fY=
2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBca7fe9e5" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  did =
not exist</a>; it was just a number displayed=C2=A0on a website and produce=
d by a=C2=A0<em>random number generator</em>. Ten seconds after FTX collaps=
ed, it was possible to think =E2=80=9Cwell that happens sometimes at levera=
ged financial institutions.=E2=80=9D A year later, it was not.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other, and frankly bigger, problem is that=
 I was not on the jury.=C2=A0And for a normal person who does not love fina=
ncial complexity and have a soft spot=C2=A0for fraud, this case was very ve=
ry very very very very very simple.=C2=A0Obviously a lot of people =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0not just Bankman-Fried=C2=A0but also the prosecutors, journalists,=
 etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0have some incentive to make it seem complicated.=C2=A0=
But all that you actually need to tell a jury is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Customers deposited billions of dolla=
rs at FTX.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Bankman-Fried spent a w=
hole lot of it on baubles like Bahamas beachfront real estate, political do=
nations, Tom Brady, etc.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The custo=
mers asked for their money back and it wasn=E2=80=99t there.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is just no coming back from that, you kn=
ow? Bankman-Fried did not: <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDMvc3BlZWR5LWJhbmttYW4tZnJpZWQtdmVyZGljdC1pcy11bnVzYWwtZm9yL=
WJpZy13aGl0ZS1jb2xsYXItY2FzZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVk=
aXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDYmdXRtX2NhbXB=
haWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3a41ae73" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Last=C2=
=A0Thursday</a>, after four weeks of trial and less than five hours of deli=
beration, the jury came back with a verdict of =E2=80=9Cobviously guilty,=
=C2=A0come on.=E2=80=9D Ernest Hemingway famously describes a character goi=
ng bankrupt =E2=80=9Cgradually, then suddenly,=E2=80=9D and everyone always=
 quotes that about every corporate bankruptcy; Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s lawy=
er said it about FTX in his closing argument. But it also describes his con=
viction: The slow accumulation of evidence, the quick and obvious decision.=
<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: trans=
parent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is one more problem with the =E2=80=9Cba=
nk run=E2=80=9D defense: FTX was not a bank. Ordinarily, when you run a hig=
hly leveraged financial institution, and it collapses, and you say =E2=80=
=9Cah well that=E2=80=99s the way things sometimes go at highly leveraged f=
inancial institutions,=E2=80=9D you were running a <em>regulated</em> finan=
cial=C2=A0institution. The thing you were running =E2=80=94=C2=A0a bank, a =
commodities futures exchange =E2=80=94=C2=A0served some social purpose, and=
 the leverage you provided was an essential part of that purpose. So regula=
tors allow it, but uneasily: They keep an eye on you, they monitor your ris=
ks, they don=E2=80=99t let you lend all of your depositors=E2=80=99 money t=
o one affiliated hedge fund, etc. There are rules to keep the customer mone=
y safe, and they also serve to keep=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>safe: Sometimes =
banks blow up, but if you ran your bank according to the rules, you don=E2=
=80=99t generally go to jail for its failure.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Running a crypto futures exchange in the Baham=
as is not like that. It=E2=80=99s not that there were no rules, exactly; Ba=
nkman-Fried certainly found a lot of rules to break. But there was not a ma=
ture regulatory environment, and the people running FTX seem to have though=
t that they could make up the rules as they went. Nor was there much of a s=
ocial purpose to what Bankman-Fried was up to: For all of FTX=E2=80=99s Sup=
er Bowl ads urging people to get into crypto, Bankman-Fried never really ar=
gued that he was doing anything useful. FTX was not channeling money from s=
avers into productive businesses. He was providing a casino for crypto gamb=
lers, taking a cut of their money and using it for=C2=A0effective altruism =
and marketing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When it turned out that he was taking, not a c=
ut of their money, but =E2=80=A6=C2=A0kind of =E2=80=A6=C2=A0all of it, the=
n that just looks like the purest possible fraud. In happier times, Bankman=
-Fried once <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/332741=
79.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtM=
jUvc2FtLWJhbmttYW4tZnJpZWQtZGVzY3JpYmVkLXlpZWxkLWZhcm1pbmctYW5kLWxlZnQtbWF0=
dC1sZXZpbmUtc3R1bm5lZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWV=
tYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW=
1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB779dfecc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  described to me<=
/a>=C2=A0the crypto tokens that his exchange traded with incredible cynicis=
m, and I said: =E2=80=9CYou're just like, well, I'm in the Ponzi business a=
nd it's pretty good.=E2=80=9D (=E2=80=9CI think that=E2=80=99s a pretty rea=
sonable response,=E2=80=9D he said.) When the Ponzi business collapses, tho=
ugh, it=E2=80=99s pretty bad.</p>
