t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;">  wrote last month</a> that =E2=80=9Cprivate=
 credit=E2=80=9D as a category feels new and different from the main existi=
ng categories of corporate credit (leveraged loans, bonds), but that over t=
ime I expect it to converge. (Just as loans and bonds, which used to have d=
ifferent lenders and uses, have converged.) I speculated=C2=A0that =E2=80=
=9Csometime within the next, like, three years, I am going to be writing ab=
out a story like =E2=80=98Company X is launching a marketplace to allow pri=
vate credit lenders to trade loans.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D Right now private cre=
dit is a fairly=C2=A0<em>illiquid=C2=A0</em>asset class, which offers attra=
ctive returns in part because you=E2=80=99re getting <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjcvc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktaXMtb24=
tZHJ1Z3M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc2=
91cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf76cbfb7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  an illiquidity premium</a>, bu=
t in fairly short order=C2=A0someone will be like =E2=80=9Cehh I=E2=80=99d =
rather have the liquidity.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today at Bloomberg, Laura Benitez and Silas Br=
own <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.25941=
2/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDYvcHJpd=
mF0ZS1jcmVkaXQtYXBvbGxvLWFyZXMtdGlrZWhhdS1mYWNpbmctbGltaXRzLW9uLXdoby10aGV5=
LWNhbi1idXktZnJvbT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTA2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWl=
sJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbm=
V5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0be1af30" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  write about liquidit=
y in the private credit market</a>. I mean, they are writing about the liqu=
idity of <em>limited partner stakes in private credit funds</em>, not of th=
e individual loans, but still:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Buyers including Apollo Global Management, Are=
s Management and Tikehau Capital have raised billions to spend on so-called=
 =E2=80=9Csecondary=E2=80=9D deals, when an investor in a private credit fu=
nd decides to sell their stake early. But in some cases they=E2=80=99re bei=
ng excluded from lists of approved acquirers by the firms who run the funds=
, according to people with knowledge of the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">While secondary sales have been increasing of =
late, restricted-buyer lists threaten to hobble efforts to make private cre=
dit more liquid. Giant insurance and pension firms have been piling into th=
e asset class recently, prompting worries at the Bank of England, European =
Union and International Monetary Fund about how easily they=E2=80=99d be ab=
le to sell out of their exposure in a crunch.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Private credit investors need the consent of a=
 fund=E2=80=99s manager =E2=80=94 known as the general partner =E2=80=94 be=
fore they can sell their holding. But some GPs have been reluctant to let c=
lose rivals buy stakes because they fear it would allow them too good a vie=
w of the inner workings of their portfolios. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Although investors understand this asset class=
 is by its nature illiquid =E2=80=94 usually involving closed-end vehicles =
with caps on withdrawals that make private corporate loans =E2=80=94 the pr=
omise of a robust secondary market has reassured some that their exposure c=
an be better managed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The private credit market, which has boomed as=
 investment banks retreated from the business of lending money to risky com=
panies, is yet to be fully tested in a crisis. And its ability to liquidate=
 holdings is a key danger highlighted by regulatory bodies such as the EU, =
whose questions are surfacing just as insurance and pension funds plan to i=
ncrease holdings in the asset class.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMzEvYmFkLXBhc3N3b3Jkcy1hcmUtc2VjdXJpdGllcy1mcmF1ZD9j=
bXBpZD1CQkQxMTA2MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV=
3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB16290fd9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">  view</a> of private credit <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDIvdGhlLWJhbmtzLWFyZS=
13aGVyZS10aGUtbW9uZXktaXNuLXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZ=
Gl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTA2JnV0bV9jYW1w=
YWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB61162671" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  continues=
</a> to be =E2=80=9Cif someone is going to be making long-term loans that t=
hey have to hold to maturity, it=E2=80=99s good for that lender to be a pen=
sion fund or life insurer with long-term funding, and private credit is sor=
t of a jazzy description for <em>that</em>,=E2=80=9D but apparently everyon=
e else=E2=80=99s view is more complicated.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere, here <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/33274179.259412/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmV0aW50ZXJlc3Qu=
Y28vcC9wcml2YXRlLWxlbmRpbmc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB03631f21" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Marc=
 Rubinstein on private credit</a>. He quotes Apollo=E2=80=99s Marc Rowan ma=
king the point that one reason for the boom in private credit is the worsen=
ing liquidity in public credit markets:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBy some estimates, dealer=
 capital =E2=80=93 the capital that facilitates trading =E2=80=93 is roughl=
y 10% today of what it was in 2008.=E2=80=9D Yet markets are three times th=
e size. Rowan sees last year=E2=80=99s breakdown in the UK liability-driven=
 investment (LDI) pension industry as the kind of thing that=E2=80=99s inev=
itable in a less liquid public market. =E2=80=9CIt will not surprise me goi=
ng forward to see liquidity challenged, public markets challenged, and inve=
stors beginning to understand that liquidity only exists on the way up and =
does not exist on the way down,=E2=80=9D says Rowan. =E2=80=9CWe should exp=
ect a more volatile, less liquid world in public markets.=E2=80=9D</p></blo=
ckquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are not happy with bond market liquidit=
y anyway, the illiquidity in private credit will be less daunting.</p>
